ArcFlow — license scope (updated 2026-05-14)

ArcFlow is distributed as two layers with two distinct licenses:

  1. THIS REPOSITORY (ozinc/arcflow) — MIT License
     Covers the contents of this repository: cookbook recipes,
     SDK source code, install scripts, MCP server reference, React
     bindings, public documentation, JSON-RPC protocol specification,
     example apps, and accompanying tooling. All files in this repo
     are MIT-licensed unless individually marked otherwise.

  2. ARCFLOW CORE BINARY RUNTIME — Proprietary Free Runtime License
     The runtime binary (`arcflow`, `arcflow-daemon`, `arcflow-mcp`,
     language-binding shared libraries) is a proprietary product of
     OZ Global Inc., distributed free-to-use under the terms in
     LICENSE-CORE.md (this repository).

The headline: build with ArcFlow freely, including commercial use,
within the Free Use Limits documented at oz.com/pricing. The MIT
license below applies to the open-source layer in this repo only.

Plain-English Q&A: see LICENSE-FAQ.md
Engine binary license:   see LICENSE-CORE.md

